{
  "stem": "25639.11",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the book arrived, and I was wondering if could it possibly be this doctor?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were many doctors in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And sure enough, I read this book with so much eagerness, as you can well imagine.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was Dr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Gisi from Budapest, and I've learned so much about her that I didn't know before who sent me back to my mother in Auschwitz, to save my life.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she wrote in this book that she, she is now a pediatrician, and she is in Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that she has given birth to hundreds-- I don't remember how many hundreds-- of children to make up for all of those that she has taken away in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Gisella Perl.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "P-E-R-L.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There's no A, Perl.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She died a couple of years ago, I read in the paper.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the name of her book?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was simply incredible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There is one item that I forgot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was going to get you the name of, of the general manager of engineering at the Continental Gummi Werke in Hanover.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Jurgen, J-U-R-G-E-N, Robisch, R-O-B-I-S-C-H.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a very nice gentleman, and he told us that he was only three years old at the time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he knows nothing about this-- about this period, and that, as I have mentioned earlier, he suggested that we go to another person, Dr. von Herz-- that means from the heart in English.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so, that correspondence has dried up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I guess this just about sums up my history.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
